******
The Americas
------------
[4] USA (Rockland County, New York)
Date: Fri 24 May 2013
Source: JTA (Jewish Telegraph Agency) [edited]
http://www.jta.org/2013/05/24/news-opinion/united-states/measles-outbreak-in-orthodox-community-in-nys-rockland-county


Public health officials discovered a case of measles at a kosher grocery store in the Orthodox community of Spring Valley, New York. The Rockland County Health Department advised those who were at the Hatzlacha Grocery Store, on 80 W Spring St, between 1:30 and 4:30 pm on Wednesday [22 May 2013] to contact their doctor.

High risk groups for measles include pregnant women, infants less than 6 months old, immunocompromised individuals, or anyone who has not been vaccinated against the disease.

Spring Valley is one of several densely populated Orthodox towns in the county, which is located about 45 minutes north of Manhattan.

